{{Infobox football biography |name = Diadié Diarra |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|1|23|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Paris]], France |height = {{height|m=1.80}}<ref name = "NFT"/> |position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] |currentclub = [[FC Gueugnon|Gueugnon]] |clubnumber = |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = 2010–2011 |clubs1 = [[FC Mantes|Mantes]] |caps1 = 7 |goals1 = 0 |years2 = 2011–2013 |clubs2 = [[Valenciennes FC|Valenciennes B]] |caps2 = 30 |goals2 = 1 |years3 = 2013–2014 |clubs3 = [[Amiens AC]] |caps3 = 19 |goals3 = 1 |years4 = 2014–2015 |clubs4 = [[RC Épernay Champagne|Épernay Champagne]] |caps4 = 14 |goals4 = 0 |years5 = 2015–2016 |clubs5 = [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre B]] |caps5 = 22 |goals5 = 0 |years6 = 2016– |clubs6 = [[FC Gueugnon|Gueugnon]] |caps6 = 20 |goals6 = 3 |nationalyears1 = 2017– |nationalteam1 = [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]] |nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |club-update = 17:38, 21 April 2017 (UTC) |ntupdate = 15:40, 20 April 2017 (UTC) }} '''Diadié Diarra''' (born 23 January 1993) is [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[FC Gueugnon|Gueugnon]], as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. Born in France, he represents [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]] at international level.
