'''Gowran Park''' is a horse [[race course]] in [[County Kilkenny]], [[Ireland]]. It is located in the Annely Estate near the village of [[Gowran]].The first meeting was held in 1914.<ref>[http://www.arts-sport-tourism.gov.ie/publications/release.asp?ID=270 Speech by Minister O'Donoghue at the opening of the new grandstand at Gowran Park racecourse<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and the first ever racecourse commentary in Ireland took place here in 1952.
Gowran Park hosts 16 race days throughout the year with both [[National Hunt]] and [[Flat racing|Flat]] meetings.
The racing season at Gowran Park has quality fixtures spread evenly throughout the year starting with the Thyestes Handicap Chase in January.
