[[File:GBWheelchairRugbyLogo.jpg|right|200px]]
The '''Great Britain Wheelchair Rugby Limited (GBWR)''' is a [[non-profit organisation]] and the [[sports governing body|governing body]] for [[wheelchair rugby]] in [[Great Britain]].  The organisation represents Great Britain in [[International Wheelchair Rugby Federation|IWRF]] and the [[Great Britain national wheelchair rugby team|national wheelchair rugby team]] in the [[British Paralympic Association]].

The organisation is responsible for the selection and training of the team that represent Great Britain in international tournaments, including the [[World Wheelchair Rugby Championships|IWRF World Championships]] and [[Wheelchair rugby at the Summer Paralympics|Games of the Paralympiad]] and the [[IWRF European Championship|qualifiers]] therefore, as well as for the promotion of the sport amongst prospective players, [[spectator sports|spectator]]s, and [[fan (aficionado)|fan]]s.

