{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Ken Pridgeon Stadium | image = Pridgeon Stadium in Cypress, Texas.png | caption =Pridgeon Stadium before a game in 2016. | location = 12550 Windfern Rd. A, Houston, TX 77064 | coordinates = {{Coord|29|56|8.73|N|95|34|11.76|W|type:edu_region:US-TX|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | opened = 1977 | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Cypress-Fairbanks Independent School District]] | operator = Cypress-Fairbanks Independent School District | surface = | capacity = 11,000 | tenants = }}
'''Ken Pridgeon Stadium''' is an outdoor American football stadium located in [[Houston, Texas]]. The stadium was built in 1977 and, along with [[Richard E. Berry Educational Support Center|Cy-Fair FCU Stadium]], serves as the home field for all [[Cypress-Fairbanks Independent School District]] varsity football games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berrycenter.net/about/venues|title=Berry Center - About Us - Venues|publisher=[[Richard E. Berry Educational Support Center]]|website=berrycenter.net|accessdate=11 July 2016}}</ref>
In May 2014, as part of a US $1.2 billion bond referendum, the stadium received $40 million for upgrades and renovations that are scheduled to be completed in two parts. Early renovations included parking lot improvements of [[LED lighting]], new concrete in parking and driveways in the complex, as well as underground drainage. Later renovations, completed between December 2016 and January 2017, include a new [[natatorium]] expected to seat 950 people, a new two-story press box, new ticket booths, restrooms, concessions stand, and an elevator that goes up to the press box. The Oldest [[American Football]] stadium in the [[Cypress-Fairbanks Independent School District]] aside from [[Cy-Fair FCU Stadium]].
