{{Infobox football biography | name = Kyle Casciaro | image = Kyle Casciaro.jpg | caption = | fullname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1987|12|2|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Gibraltar]] | height = | currentclub = [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]]<ref>[https://www.gibraltarfa.com/domestic-football/second-division]</ref> | clubnumber = 5 | position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]], [[Forward (association football)|forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2010–2013 | clubs1 = [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2013–2017 | clubs2 = [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] | caps2 = 77 | goals2 = 37 | years3 = 2018– | clubs3 = [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] | caps3 = 4 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2018 | clubs4 = → [[F.C. Olympique 13|FC Olympique 13]] (loan) | caps4 = 6 | goals4 = 0 <!--all match stats are taken from the GFA website's fixtures/results page. There is no single appearances page, so refer to each individual match page--> | nationalyears1 = 2011 | nationalteam1 = Gibraltar XI <small>([[Non-FIFA international football|Non-FIFA]])</small> | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2013– | nationalteam2 = [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] | nationalcaps2 = 24 | nationalgoals2 = 1 | pcupdate = 1 October 2018 | ntupdate = 16 October 2018 }} '''Kyle Casciaro''' (born 2 December 1987) is a former Gibraltarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]], and the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] national team, where he plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]].
==Club career== Casciaro came through the ranks of [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] with brothers [[Ryan Casciaro|Ryan]] and [[Lee Casciaro|Lee]], becoming ever present in the dominant Red Imps team that won 6 of its 14 consecutive league titles from 2010 to 2016. After suffering a serious injury in summer 2017, he retired from football. However, in January 2018 he came out of retirement, re-joining Lincoln while joining [[F.C. Olympique 13|FC Olympique 13]] on loan for the rest of the season, in order to regain match fitness.
==International career== Casciaro made his international debut with Gibraltar on 19 November 2013 in a 0–0 home draw with [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://footballgibraltar.wordpress.com/2013/11/20/gibraltar-0-0-slovakia-extended-match-report/ | title=Gibraltar 0-0 Slovakia – extended match report | publisher=footballgibraltar.wordpress.com | accessdate=21 November 2013}}</ref> This was Gibraltar's first game since being admitted to [[UEFA]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/qualifiers/news/newsid=2024868.html | title=Gibraltar hold Slovakia in maiden international | publisher=www.uefa.com | accessdate=21 November 2013}}</ref> He was the first Gibraltarian footballer to score a winning goal at senior international level since joining UEFA, having struck against [[Malta national football team|Malta]] in June 2014.
