{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2011}} {{Infobox country at games | NOC = KGZ | NOCname = [[National Olympic Committee of the Republic of Kyrgyzstan]] | oldcode = | year = 1998 | date = | games = Asian Games | location = [[Bangkok]] | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | officials = | gold = 0 | silver = 3 | bronze = 3 | rank = 24 | appearances = auto | seealso = | website = }}
'''[[Kyrgyzstan]]''' participated in the [[1998 Asian Games]] held in [[Bangkok]], Thailand from December 6, 1998 to December 20, 1998. Athletes from Kyrgyzstan succeeded in winning three silvers and same number of bronzes, making total six medals. Kyrgyzstan finished at 24th position in a medal table.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ocasia.org/Game/MWinner.aspx?AMWCode=17&GCode=1 | title=Over all medal standings &ndash; Bangkok 1998 | publisher=ocasia.org | work=[[Olympic Council of Asia]] | accessdate=June 12, 2011}}</ref>
