{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Stade Ali Zouaoui | former names = | image = [[File:Ali Zouaoui stadium.JPG|250px]] | location = [[Tunis]], [[Tunisia]] | built = | opened = | closed = 1999 | renovated = | surface = Grass | tenants = [[JS Kairouan]] | seating_capacity = 15,000 }} '''Stade Ali Zouaoui''' ({{Lang-ar|ملعب علي الزواوي}}) is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Kairouan]], [[Tunisia]]. It was used by [[football (soccer)|football]] team [[Jeunesse Sportive Kairouanaise]] until 1999. The stadium holds 15,000 people. It was named after economist and football executive originated from [[Kairouan Governorate]] [[Ali Zouaoui]].
